[0.045, "o", "\r\nFATAL ERROR: Could not find my_print_defaults\r\n\r\nThe following directories were searched:\r\n\r\n    /usr--datadir=/var/lib/mysql/bin\r\n    /usr--datadir=/var/lib/mysql/extra\r\n\r\nIf you compiled from source, you need to either run 'make install' to\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "copy the software into the correct location ready for operation.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "If you don't want to do a full install, you can use the --srcdir\r\noption to only install the mysql database and privilege tables.\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "If you are using a binary release, you must either be at the top\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "level of the extracted archive, or pass the --basedir option\r\npointing to that location.\r\n\r\n"]
[0.000, "o", "The latest information about mariadb-install-db is available at\r\n"]
[0.001, "o", "https://mariadb.com/kb/en/installing-system-tables-mysql_install_db\r\n"]
