[0.000, "o", "If your scripts have to deal with files from Macintosh systems,\u001b[10;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "or you are running on a Mac and need to deal with files from\r\u001b[11d"]
[0.001, "o", "; unix or win32 systems, setting this flag will cause PHP to\r\u001b[12d; automatically detect the EOL character in those files so that\u001b[13;3Hfgets() and file() will work regardless of the source of the file.\r\u001b[14d; https://php.net/auto-detect-line-endings\r\u001b[15d;auto_detect_line_endings = Off\r\u001b[16d\u001b[K\u001b[17d;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\u001b[18;3HDynamic Extensions ;\r\u001b[19d;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\u001b[20d\u001b[K\u001b[21d; If you wish to have an extension loaded automatically, use the following\u001b[22;3Hsyntax:\u001b[K\u001b[23;3H\u001b[K\u001b[24d  \u001b[30m\u001b[43mextension=\u001b[39;49m\u001b[m\u000fmodulename\u001b[K\u001b[25;3H\u001b[K\u001b[26dFor example:\u001b[K\u001b[27;3H\u001b[K\u001b[28d  extension=mysqli\u001b[K\r\u001b[29d;\u001b[K\u001b[30d\b; When the extension library to load is not located in the default extension\u001b[31;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "directory, You may specify an absolute path to the library file:\u001b[K\u001b[32;3H"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[K\u001b[33d"]
[0.000, "o", "  extension=/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\u001b[K\u001b[34;3H\u001b[K\u001b[35d"]
[0.000, "o", "Note : The syntax used in previous PHP versions ('extension=<ext>.so' and\u001b[36;3H'extension='php_<ext>.dll') is supported for legacy reasons and may be\r\u001b[37d; deprecated in a future PHP major version. So, when it is possible, please\r\u001b[38d; move to the new ('extension=<ext>) syntax.\u001b[39;3H"]
